==English==

===Etymology===

Latin ''erumpens'', to break forth

===Adjective===
'''erumpent'''

# Which emerges, or bursts through.
#*'''1989''', [[w:Nick Cave|Nick Cave]], ''[[w:And the Ass Saw the Angel|And the Ass Saw the Angel]]''
#*: The sun spun aloft, an '''erumpent''' orb of balling glory thrilling the blue sky with its brilliance.

